title: ISC badminton tournament: Vineesh Mathew, Rajesh Pillai secure upset win
text:
ISC badminton tournament: Vineesh Mathew, Rajesh Pillai secure upset win October 05, 2015 
The unseeded duo of Vineesh Mathew and Rajesh Pillai shocked the second-seeded pair of Ghafoor and Sudhin 21-19, 21-19 in the third round of the men's open doubles event at the annual badminton tournament, organised by Indian Social Club (ISC) Muscat, on Saturday. 
In the other matches, the top-seeded pair of Albert V R and Mohammed Harouz got the better of Anoop P R and Mohammed Salim 21-15, 21-18 and Prabhu A R and Niyas N downed Shivadas P and Sajeev Surendran 21-11, 21-19 to book a spot in the quarterfinals. 
Other results: (second round): Percy Pereira-P T Francis beat Senthil-Balasubramanian 21-4, 21-8; Vinod Abraham-Sony beat Vijay-Mohammed al Fajwani 19-21, 21-16, 21-16; Cyril William-Sudheer beat Ratheesh-Shivaram 21-18, 21-17; Mohammed Amir-Amjad beat Sunil Kumar-Shaiju 21-16, 26-24; Albert-Harouz beat Rahim-Mannan 21-11, 21-6; Anoop-Salim beat Yogesh Narula-Babu Said 22-20, 21-14.
